    <briefdescription>
<para>The sound module handles dynamically allocated one-channel audio signals, providing functions for in-memory initialisation and copying, as well as loading and storing sounds from and to WAV files. </para>    </briefdescription>
    <detaileddescription>
<para>All in-memory sounds are expected to have a fixed sample rate, defined by SAMPLERATE. The <ref refid="group__sound_1ga8cbd5d359fdafc96c1812b101985bcb2" kindref="member">sound_resample()</ref> function enables the conversion of a sound of a different sample rate to the expected one.</para><para>If given an already initialised sound, all initialisation functions deallocate the old data before proceeding.</para><para><simplesect kind="author"><para>Dragomir Ioan (trupples) </para></simplesect>
<simplesect kind="author"><para>Dan Cristian </para></simplesect>
</para>    </detaileddescription>
